  "texts": [
    "The global impacts of AI technology and ensuing regulatory challenges necessitate international responses, implying the need to Government & Regulatory Bodies Governments and regulatory bodies play a crucial role in setting and supervising safety standards and regulations, as evidenced by IAEA's approach where establishing standardized safety standards and an independent supervisory system are regulatory imperatives.",
    "Companies developing, producing, and selling AI technologies and products must adhere to regulatory standards and bear the responsibility of providing safe products and services.",
    "This necessitates the establishment of independent audit and evaluation systems within each corporation.",
    "Research Institutions & Academia Engaged in research regarding technological advancements and associated risks, these entities provide scientific bases for regulatory directions and necessity.",
    "Cases like the Fukushima accident have underscored the importance of research institutions."
  ],
